  "body": "This is a funny one, here I'm opening the search popup:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 09-16-24](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159872135-9b71fb03-63d0-41b0-8238-556bbac0ea63.png)\r\n\r\nNow I'm opening the location menu:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 09-16-56](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159872239-ee8585b0-653f-4a69-8bf0-4c0967d3bc25.png)\r\n\r\nIt's hard to see, but notice how the backdrop got slightly darker. This is most likely because the search popup modal introduces a backdrop, and the location menu introduces another one which is then layered on top of the first one.\r\n\r\nWe can test this thesis by opening another level of the menu:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 09-18-43](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159872526-507ba316-b9fb-4424-bd6d-693995db4f15.png)\r\n\r\nIt got slightly darker again.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThe backdrop should stay the same all the time because otherwise it introduces some flickering which is not only annoying but stressful haha\r\n\r\n\r\n",
